{{Infobox Observatory}}
The '''Arcetri Observatory''' ({{lang-it|Osservatorio Astrofisico di Arcetri}}) is an astrophysical observatory located in the hilly area of [[Arcetri]] on the outskirts of [[Florence]], [[Italy]]. It is located close to [[Villa Il Gioiello]], the residence of [[Galileo Galilei]] from 1631 to 1642. Observatory staff carry out theoretical and observational astronomy as well as designing and constructing astronomical instrumentation. The observatory has been heavily involved with the following instrumentation projects:
* The [[MMT Observatory|MMT]] 6.5 m telescope * The [[Large Binocular Telescope|LBT]] 2x 8.4 m telescopes * The [[Telescopio Nazionale Galileo]] 3.5 m telescope * The [[Very Large Telescope|VLT]] telescope adaptive secondary mirror * The 1.5 m [[Gornergrat Infrared Telescope]] (TIRGO)
==See also== *[[List of solar telescopes]]
